<br>
&quot;Our first objective will be to reach the great dragon head bridge.  This bridge is guarded, but we should not have any difficulty in eluding the guards and continuing on our journey.  Once we have crossed to the mainland, we'll seek some shelter with a Coldain outpost.  This part of our journey should not take long, but the weather may factor into how far we will travel.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/13/01 11:18:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.honestevil.com/deleted_roster/hail_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> The tiny raft lands on the shoreline.<br>
<br>
Casidy persuades Taino and Febreeza to carry the still lifeless form of Crydee to the large ship awaiting them on the other side of the small island.<br>
<br>
Jzonn lead the compliment across the shoreline carefully.<br>
<br>
The air is quite frigid, and feels heavy in the lungs of the young bad.<br>
<br>
Just as Casidy turns to Jzonn to ask if they should reach the pier to the large boat, she sees a gnome before her shouting something about hurrying as the boat will be departing soon.<br>
<br>
They all hurry onboard, just as the ships mechanical engine rushes to life, and begins to churn through the ice flow.<br>
<br>
Ice Breaker. An aptly named ship, Casidy thinks to herself, as the ship rocks and crushes making a path through the ice.<br>
<br>
"Crydee will be rising soon, and he will likely not be too happy at me for knocking him out." a small smirk crosses her face as Casidy turns to Febreeza "I think if we can find some cookies about he might be satiated however."<br>
<br>
The hours onboard the vessal pass quickly, and off in the distance she can hear the shouts of the pirate’s announcing the boats arrival.<br>
<br>
Casidy knows she is to meet a messenger at the dock, a cousin of hers... Kristav.<br>
<br>
She has not seen Kristav in years, and is wondering if she will even recognize the bard.<br>
<br>
Sighing softly to herself she gathers her things an looks wayward off in the distance.<br>
<br>
They reach the docks and all of the party disembark.<br>
<br>
Checking through her backpack, Casidy speaks softly to her party. "Are we all ready to proceed?"<br>
